article.description: Richmond with 4 in double figures, beats UMass 56-53
article.headline: Richmond with 4 in double figures, beats UMass 56-53
article.linkText: Richmond with 4 in double figures, beats UMass 56-53
article.story: AMHERST, Mass. -- Kendall Anthony scored 14 points to lead four in double figures as Richmond beat Massachusetts 56-53 on Wednesday night for its fifth straight victory. Richmond led 27-25 at the break, and opened the second half on a 10-2 surge to make it 37-27 and the Spiders led the rest of the way. Terry Allen scored 13 points, T.J. Cline had 12 and ShawnDre' Jones chipped in 11 for Richmond (18-12, 11-6 Atlantic 10). Donte Clark converted a three-point play to pull UMass within 48-45 with 1:40 to play. Back-to-back layups stretched the Spiders lead to six with 45 second left. The Minutemen's Cady Lalanne answered with a tip-in bucket, but Allen scored a layup and Anthony made a pair of free throws to seal it for the Spiders. Lalanne led UMass (17-13, 10-7) with 14 points and Clark, who added 12, hit a 3 at the buzzer to end it.
